Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry all produce. Peel and mince or grate @ginger{1%thumb}.

In a #small pot{}, combine @jasmine rice{1/2%cup}, @water{3/4%cup}, and a big pinch of @salt{}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}. Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

While rice cooks, toss @green beans{6%ounce} on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @vegetable oil{}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}. Roast on top rack until browned and tender, ~{12-15%minutes}.

Meanwhile, pat @chicken cutlets{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}; season all over with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Heat a drizzle of @vegetable oil{2%teaspoon} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add chicken and cook until browned and cooked through, ~{3-5%minutes} per side. Turn off heat; transfer to a #plate{}.

Add half the ginger (or more if you want an extra kick!) to same pan over medium heat. Cook until fragrant, ~{30%seconds}. Add @apricot jam{2%tablespoon}, @chicken stock concentrate{1%unit}, and @water{1/4%cup}. Cook, stirring, until thickened, ~{1-2%minutes}. Turn off heat; stir in @butter{1%tablespoon} until melted.

Fluff rice with a #fork{}; stir in @butter{1%tablespoon} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Divide rice, chicken, and green beans between plates. Drizzle chicken with sauce and serve.